Additionally, the paper discusses the learning algorithm and demonstrates its effectiveness through various examples, which are common themes in the machine learning literature. 

The paper also touches upon topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with compressed latent representations of complex data, which are often used in these fields. 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the flexibility of individual posteriors, which is a concept related to neural networks (cs.NE). 

Finally, the paper proposes a new learning algorithm, which can be considered a contribution to the field of statistical learning (cs.SD).
